brands.description: Nirma is a group of companies based in the city of Ahmedabad in western India that manufactures products ranging from cosmetics, soaps, detergents, salt, soda ash, LAB and Injectables. brands.description: NEC Corporation is a Japanese multinational provider of information technology (IT) services and products, with its headquarters in Minato, Tokyo, Japan. NEC provides IT and network solutions to business enterprises, communications services providers and to government agencies, and has also been the biggest PC vendor in Japan since the 1980s.
brands.name: NEC

namedLocations.description: Gujarat (/ˌɡʊdʒəˈrɑːt/, Gujarati: [ˈɡudʒəɾɑt] ) is a state on the western coast of India with a coastline of 1,600 km (990 mi) – most of which lies on the Kathiawar peninsula – and a population in excess of 60 million. It is the sixth largest Indian state by area and the ninth largest state by population. Gujarat is bordered by Rajasthan to the northeast, Daman and Diu to the south, Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Maharashtra to the southeast, Madhya Pradesh to the east, and the Arabian Sea and the Pakistani province of Sindh to the west. Its capital city is Gandhinagar, while its largest city is Ahmedabad. The Gujarati-speaking people of India are indigenous to the state. The economy of Gujarat is the fifth-largest state economy in India with ₹14.96 lakh crore (US$220 billion) in gross domestic product and a per capita GDP of ₹157,000 (US$2,300). Gujarat ranks fifteenth among Indian states in human development index.
namedLocations.name: Gujarat

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the Onprint Shop Quote Management tutorial series.
This video is about setting up the quote form fields.
In this video we will see what the quote form fields are and how to create them for existing and custom products on the front store.
When you click on the request a quote, it will take you to the request quote page with a quote form that is to be filled by customers for getting the quotation.
So the fields that make this form are called the quote form field.
As you can see there are two options for the product type, existing products and custom products.

Existing is for the products that are available for sale on your website and which are listed and custom product is the one which is not listed on your website and it is a completely customizable product.
So the fields can differ based on the product type selection.
These fields can be created from the admin panel.
So let's get started.
In the Admin panel, navigate to the Store Configuration section and then click on the Manage Form fields.
In the listing, you can see the Size, Paper, stock, and Lamination fields listed.
These are created for custom or quote products that we already saw on the front store in the Request Quote form.
To create a new form field, click on the Add button from the top right corner.
To start.
Select the store from the drop down menu.
Let's create a form field for coding.
Type so enter coding in the title.
Add the description if you want to share any information related to the field.
Next you have to choose for which form you are creating this field.
Is it for the quotes form for Hire designer or the template form.
As we are creating this field for quotes, select quotes.
Here.
The product specific attribute setting allows you to select the product for which you are creating this form field.
If you are creating this field for any specific product then first choose specific products and then select the products and assign them in the list.
The first option will be Custom Quote product as one of the products.
If you are creating the field for all products then select all products.
Let's select Custom Quote product here.
If you have added the description for this field and enable the display description in pop up setting, then the description will appear in the pop up.
You can set the sorting order and enable the status of this field to display on the quote request page.
The next setting is the field type.
We have options similar to what we have for creating additional options.
Let's create a drop down type of form field and make the validation mandatory.
Finally, add the attributes for the field.
Select one default option, enable the status of all the attributes, and then click on the Save and back button.
Let's verify this on the front end.
Return to the request quote page of the front store and refresh the page.
Select the custom in the product type and you can see the coding field in the form with all the four attributes for selection.
And that's it.
You have created a form field for the request quotes form successfully.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
